exercises.title: Lateral Raise (Dumbbell)
exercises.notes: Keep the movement slow and controlled; avoid using momentum, especially as your shoulders start to burn.

exercises.title: Seated Calf Raise
exercises.notes: Slowly lower your heels to the floor for an intense calf stretch at the bottom and pause briefly instead of ‘bouncing.’

exercises.title: Warm Up
exercises.notes: Do a full-body warm-up consisting of dynamic exercises like leg swings, arm circles, jumping jacks, and high knees.

exercises.title: Pull Up
exercises.notes: Add extra weight to yourself only if you can do at least 15 bodyweight pull-ups. Train to an RPE 8-9 (leaving one to two reps in the tank at the end of each set).

exercises.title: Incline Bench Press (Dumbbell)
exercises.notes: Slowly lower the dumbbells as much as you can to your sides. The goal is to feel a good stretch in your upper chest. You can also do chest presses on a machine where the handles move forward and up.

exercises.title: Hip Thrust (Machine)
exercises.notes: Doing hip thrusts on a machine reduces the need to balance all the time. However, you can also do these with a barbell if your gym doesn’t have this machine.

exercises.title: Upright Row (Barbell)
exercises.notes: Use a wider grip if it feels more comfortable. You can also do these on a cable machine with a straight bar if that feels better on your shoulders and traps.

exercises.title: Standing Calf Raise (Machine)
exercises.notes: Slowly lower your heels to the floor for an intense calf stretch at the bottom and pause briefly instead of ‘bouncing.’

exercises.title: Bench Press (Barbell)
exercises.notes: Control the bar on the way down and touch your lower chest. Pause briefly and press from a dead stop instead of bouncing the bar. Add more warm-up sets if needed.

exercises.title: Bent Over Row (Barbell)
exercises.notes: Slowly lower the weight to feel a stretch in your upper back. Pull in one fluid motion.

exercises.title: Leg Press (Machine)
exercises.notes: Placing your feet close together and lower on the platform forces a greater knee range of motion, which leads to better quadriceps (front thigh muscle) activation.

exercises.title: Shoulder Press (Dumbbell)
exercises.notes: Keep your abs engaged for stability, and press the dumbbells up and in. Lower the weights until your elbows are slightly below shoulder level.

exercises.title: Bicep Curl (Barbell)
exercises.notes: Slowly lower the bar until your arms are straight, and squeeze your biceps at the top.

exercises.notes: If possible, place the balls of your feet on an elevated object to train through a longer range of motion. Do the single-leg version for an extra challenge. Train to an RPE 9 (leaving one rep in the tank at the end of each set).
